        "ratings": [
            {
                "comment": "Jenny is really sweet and caring. It honestly felt like a high school class again, getting to know everyone in the class and writing paper after paper. However, she doesn't grade hard, and is very understanding. Just do the assignments on time and you'll get an A or AB!",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Jenny was a good teacher overall. There is a lot of writing in this class, as can be expected in a college level English class. She wasn't the best at communicating assignments to the class and what homework was assigned. We had to buy a book at the beginning of the semester, but I never read a single page of it, as it wasn't needed.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 4
            },
            {
                "comment": "Jenny is a wonderful professor. She is very approachable and she cares about her students and their learning. I never feel like our assignments are useless or busy-work, and overall I've learned a lot.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
